Name: Queensway
Phrase: We've managed to get down here. But there still doesn't seem to be any lights...

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Is this the love nest? The secret room that would make Queensway blush.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Miss Yoshino, seriously... Do you know what a love nest is?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yes. It's where two people who love each other make love.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: It-It's not always a place where people make love!

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Shut up, both of you. You two can make love only after we turn on the lights.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Sorry...

Name: Versailles
Phrase: 'It's kind of a strange place. I didn't expect Victoria to be right, it really was a torture chamber...

Name: Victoria
Phrase: No, not a torture chamber. This is perhaps a dungeon.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: A dungeon?

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Yes. Inmates or POWs are kept in these cells. You can see the bars here. I think this whole room is one dungeon.

Name: Putra
Phrase: So we're in a dungeon right after you go down the Hole... It's kind of sad. This is such a magnificent castle.

Name: Putra
Phrase: Huh, but wait? Wait... I understand inmates, but what's a POW?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Short for 'Prisoners of War'.

Name: Putra
Phrase: So this castle is...

Name: Victoria
Phrase: This is not a castle, but a fortress. It was built in the middle of a long war. And this war was not against Phantom Mist, but against men.

Name: Putra
Phrase: So a fight against humans.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: That kind of warfare exists. I don't know when this castle was built, but I'm sure people still fight each other.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Did the inmates or prisoners of war in this dungeon summon us? If so, it is most likely a trap.

Name: Putra
Phrase: But the woman just now said she would 'turn on the lights'. Isn't she going to help us?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: That's why I said it could be a trap. What if we unleash something bad?
Don't worry. I have no intention of harming you.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: D-did someone say something?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Nobody said anything.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: No? Then I must have heard wrong.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: But it's true, I heard strange voices in the back.
Please come straight to the back through the grating. I would like you to open my prison.
In the darkness, with no lights, the woman's voice was heard again from the back of the dungeon. "I don't mean you any harm.

In my experience, saying 'yes, I understand' and do as I am told obviously is trouble. Unlocking the dungeon means releasing the captives. Releasing inmates and prisoners of war at this stage, when we don't know the purpose of this castle, is risky.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: But we are not able to progress considering the status quo. It seems that the other side is alone, so why not challenge them on the premise of a fight?

Name: Versailles
Phrase: That's a good point, but only if we have light. It's dangerous. We don't even know if our opponent is alone.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Hence I will go alone first. You will all stay here until I return. If anything should happen to me, please retreat up the stairs to the Hole.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Then I will go. I am more used to working in the dark.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: No, no. I should be the one to go here.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Why?

Name: Victoria
Phrase: That is because you are of short stature, Miss Versailles.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Wait? Did you just say 'stature'? Not 'temper'?

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Dungeons have keys and escape routes hidden higher up than you'd think, Miss Versailles. You may not be able to reach them.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Not to worry. I have my sword.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: There may be a hidden switch or something where I can only reach, even with a sword.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: That's...

Name: Paddington
Phrase: Miss Versailles, please allow Victoria to proceed from here.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Miss Paddington...

Name: Paddington
Phrase: I understand that you are concerned, Versailles. Victoria is very good at escaping and breaking out bad situations though.

Name: Paddington
Phrase: When she was locked inside Oshioki Prison, when she's fallen down a well, when both her hands and feet were bound and dropped into a fountain, Victoria still made a perfect escape on all those situations.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: I see. She has survived in extreme conditions. Meaning she's done a lot of front-line work...

Name: Paddington
Phrase: No, this all happened in our compound.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Eh...

Name: Victoria
Phrase: That's why I'm the right person for this kind of assignment. I've been recommended to this team by Lady Paddington, I hope you'll trust my infiltration ability here.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Very well. But please proceed only as far as we can hear you. I want you to keep us informed of the situation so that we can be sure you are safe, Victoria.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Verily. Please wait here for a moment, ladies and gentlemen.

Name: Paddington
Phrase: Don't worry, Miss Versailles. Victoria will make it. I'm sure she's better at these jobs than making tea or cleaning.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: I've never heard of such a maid.

Name: Paddington
Phrase: Yes I have! I'm proud of my maid!

Name: Versailles
Phrase: (I don't remember complimenting her...)

Name: Paddington
Phrase: Victoria has a tendency to charge in without really thinking things through. But on this occasion, she has thought it through and explained it to you all. It's a sign of unusual discretion. Though I think she was half-serious about your height.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: So this is really the relationship between a Divine Child and her servant. You know the minute details very well.

Name: Paddington
Phrase: Our relationship isn't of a Divine Child and a servant though. Victoria and I have been best friends since childhood♪

Name: Versailles
Phrase: The great Divine Children sure are interesting...
